From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 01:40:02 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 64/64] web-app: styled download-on-demand placeholders (type,
 thumbnail, size)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Large attachments (>140 KB in encrypted chats) arrive as a pre-message
placeholder before the real message. Upstream renders it as a plain text
line ("text [Image – 228 KiB] - Download"). This adds a per-type styled
placeholder that mirrors the "Done"-path attachment markup.

New DownloadOnDemandPlaceholder component renders the fork's thumbnail
(blob referenced by Param::File, exposed as message.file) and target size:
- image/gif/sticker: blurred thumbnail (or grey box) in the
  .message-attachment-media box with a centered download+size overlay
- video: same media box, black bg, CSS play glyph
- audio/voice: .message-attachment-audio-style row
- file: .message-attachment-generic card with extension + name
- webxdc: .webxdc card with the app icon (thumbnail or default asset)

Wired into Message.tsx's downloadState !== 'Done' branch behind the new
message.postMessageViewType field; the old plain-text path stays as the
fallback when that field is absent (old-DC senders). showAttachment is now
gated on downloadState === 'Done' so a placeholder's thumbnail is never
rendered as a real attachment card. The trailing " [Label – size]" tag core
appends to the caption is stripped since our UI shows the size itself.

postMessageViewType isn't in the pinned @deltachat/jsonrpc-client bindings
yet (core regenerates them later in the build); it's read through one typed
accessor rather than scattered casts.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
